
(1) Functional tests:

* How to install:

On Mac, using homebrew:

$ brew install phantomjs
$ brew install casperjs


(Alternatively, both can be installed with npm)

* To run all the tests:

$ casperjs test tests/*.js


(2) Acceptance tests:

First run a browser emulator:

$ java -jar -Dwebdriver.chrome.driver=chromedriver selenium-server-standalone-3.8.1.jar

or 

$  phantomjs --webdriver=8643

you can choose one of the commands below:

$ Behat/bin/behat --tags @wip -c Behat/behat.yml    # will run the scenarios tagged as @wip
$ Behat/bin/behat --tags ~@wip -c Behat/behat.yml    # will run all the scenarios but those tagged as @wip
$ Behat/bin/behat -c Behat/behat.yml    # will run all the scenarios
